    <dl class="g2 gap12" style="margin-bottom:48px">
      <div class="gl-entry"><dt>Mesoscale scaffold</dt><dd>The relatively stable community structure — broad modular organization persisting even when influence shifts across phases.</dd></div>
      <div class="gl-entry"><dt>Minimum dominating set <span class="tag">MDS</span></dt><dd>Smallest node set covering the whole graph directly or through neighbors. Defines which symptoms can serve as drivers.</dd></div>
      <div class="gl-entry"><dt>Control frequency <span class="tag">CF</span></dt><dd>Proportion of exact MDS solutions in which a symptom appears. High CF indicates repeated participation in driver-node sets.</dd></div>
      <div class="gl-entry"><dt>Avg. control frequency <span class="tag">ACF</span></dt><dd>Mean node-level CF within a module. Useful for summarizing within-module control, but less stable than AMCS under case loss.</dd></div>
      <div class="gl-entry"><dt>Avg. module control strength <span class="tag">AMCS</span></dt><dd>Directed summary of how strongly one module dominates another. This is the manuscript's primary mesoscopic control metric.</dd></div>
